<TITLE> Pilkhana court hears charges against 668 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 31 (bdnews24.com)  A special BDR court at Pilkhana heard charges Wednesday morning against border guards of the 24 Rifles Battalion accused of mutiny in February 2009. The court at the Darbar Hall, with BDR director general Major General Moinul Islam in the chair, began at around 10:13am. Charges were read out against 668 mutineers and 355 were shown arrested in the day's proceedings. The court ordered the arrest of another 313 BDR soldiers and adjourned till Thursday morning. This is the second Pilkhana trial. Trial of some 310 border guards of 36 Rifles Battalion also began last month at the same court. Over 70 people, 57 of them army officers deputed to the border force, were killed during the mutiny at Pilkhana on Feb 25-26 2009. Rebellion also spread to BDR outposts in several districts around the country. The government formed six special courts last year, including two in Dhaka, to try approximately 3,500 border guards of different battalions have been accused in 40 separate cases in connection with the mutiny and associated rebellions in other district
